This is a great airport bus service that is extremely convenient.
For just £3.50 for a single or £6 for a round-trip, it does what it advertises and gets you safely to the airport and back.
Considering the regular buses in town are cheaper but take double or triple the time, the Airlink is well worth it and is super easy and reliable, leaving every quarter hour or even more frequently in peak times.
They have a map telling you where you are at all times for the newbies to town, and they even have free wifi on board for your thirty-minute journey.

Fast (traffic incident depending, obviously), handy (runs along the main thoroughfare of Edinburgh, along Princes Street and then down Corstorphine Road) and inexpensive.
Don't really know where else I can go with this review, and the fact is I have 11 more to scribe today (I will have you Yelp Challenge) so the fact my thoughts on the Airlink are short and sweet is kind of a good thing...  Don't really know why I've held back on the 5th star.
Maybe I wanted to be entertained on my way home from the airport, as I returned from my holiday feeling depressed and freezing cold, so the addition of some young, up and coming comedians, a fluffy owl, a game of bus bingo or just copious amounts of booze might have helped.

The Airlink service is pretty awesome.
There's a timetable but you don't really need it as there are buses pretty much every 15 minutes going from outside Waverley Train Station to the Airport.
Even in morning traffic, you''ll get there in around 30 - 45 minutes.
The drivers are really friendly.
The bus is really clean, with plenty of luggage space.
The bus there was almost empty, the bus back was full, so a little cramped.
But at £6 return, when a single taxi journey to the airport will cost £20 (so £40 return) you're saving £34.
You can't really complain.
